Here are logic-building Python list questions that will help improve your problem-solving skills:

Basic Logic-Based Questions
Write a Python program to find the largest and smallest number in a list.

Reverse a list without using the built-in reverse() method.

Find the sum of all elements in a list.

Find the second largest number in a list.

Remove all even numbers from a list.

Intermediate Logic-Based Questions
Check if a list is sorted in ascending or descending order.

Rotate a list n positions to the right.

Merge two sorted lists into a single sorted list.

Remove duplicates from a list without using set().

Find the most frequently occurring element in a list.

Pattern & Arrangement-Based Problems
Given a list of numbers, replace every element with the product of all elements except itself (without using division).

Rearrange a list so that even numbers appear before odd numbers while maintaining their relative order.

Rearrange a list so that positive numbers appear before negative numbers.

Find all pairs in a list that sum to a given target value.

Find the intersection of two lists without using built-in functions.

Advanced Logic-Based Questions
Find the longest increasing subsequence in a list.

Find the missing number in a sequence from 1 to n.

Find the subarray with the maximum sum (Kadaneâ€™s Algorithm).

Given a list of integers, find three numbers whose sum is closest to zero.

Given a rotated sorted list, find the index of the minimum element.